# Construction Company Website Rules

## General

* Always generate production-ready code.
* Use Next.js App Router.
* Use TypeScript strictly.
* Never use the "any" type.
* Follow clean code principles.
* Keep components modular and reusable.
* Avoid code duplication.

## Architecture

* Use Server Components by default.
* Use Client Components only when necessary.
* Separate UI, business logic, and data fetching.
* Maintain scalable folder structure.

## Styling

* Use Tailwind CSS only.
* Follow mobile-first design.
* Use consistent spacing and typography.
* Avoid inline styles unless necessary.

## SEO

* Every page must contain:

  * Title
  * Meta description
  * Open Graph tags
  * Structured data

* Use semantic HTML elements.

* Optimize all pages for search engines.

## Performance

* Use Next.js Image component.
* Optimize images before usage.
* Lazy load non-critical content.
* Minimize client-side JavaScript.
* Maintain Lighthouse score above 90.

## Accessibility

* Use proper heading hierarchy.
* Add alt text to images.
* Support keyboard navigation.
* Use ARIA labels where appropriate.

## Security

* Never expose secrets.
* Use environment variables.
* Validate all form inputs.
* Sanitize user input.

## UI Guidelines

The website must feel:

* Premium
* Modern
* Professional
* Corporate
* Trustworthy

Avoid:

* Excessive animations
* Neon colors
* Cluttered layouts
* Overly complex interactions

## Animation

Use Framer Motion sparingly.

Preferred:

* Fade in
* Slide up
* Scroll reveal
* Hover transitions

Avoid:

* Bounce effects
* Excessive motion
* Performance-heavy animations

## Code Review Checklist

Before generating code verify:

* Responsive design
* SEO compliance
* Accessibility compliance
* TypeScript correctness
* Performance optimization
* Reusability


